ELISION.

But in a majority of the lines a further difficulty arises. Where the last syllable of a word ends in a vowel, or in m. and the first syllable of the next word begins with a vowel or h, these two syllables are elided or taken together and counted as one. Such a case is called 01151011* For example vera inquit, counts as three syllables in scansion, so also tegerem ut, clivum humo, curru haeret.
